1. Leetcode problem-215: Kth Largest Element in an array

import heapq

class Solution:
    def findKthLargest(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:
        min_heap=[]

        for num in nums:
            if len(min_heap) < k:
                heapq.heappush(min_heap,num)
            else:
                heapq.heappushpop(min_heap,num)

        return min_heap[0]

Approach:

1.Brute force: Sort the array and return the kth position from the last. But the time complexity for that approach would be o(n logn) since sorting would take that time.
2.Better Approach: Is to use a max heap. Make a max_heap with all of the numbers in the array and pop the max element k times to get the kth largest element. 
But since constructing max_heap takes o(logn) and popping k times takes o(klogn), we get the total complexity as O(n+klogn)
3.Optimal approach is to implement a min_heap and then make a min_heap with k elements. Always make sure, the size of min_heap is less than k. 
When it is getting larger than k, push and element and pop an element simultaneously and finally return the top element since it will be kth maximum.
The time com[plexity of min_hepa approach is O(nlogk) since we are iterating the array o(n) and calling pop and insert k times O(logk).
Spce Complexity would be O(k) since we are not using heapify(it does the heap operations in place).

Also, one more approach would be to use quick select algorithm. Time complexity would be O(n) but in the worst case it would be O(n^2).


        
